'''金繼'''（金継ぎ，「以金子去承繼」之意），也稱為'''金繕'''（金繕い，「以金子去修繕」之意）。<ref name=":0">{{Cite web|title=definition of Kintsugi|url=http://www.definition-of.com/kintsugi|accessdate=|author=|date=|first=|work=|publisher=}}</ref>  
 
金繼這種工藝使用數種[[漆|漆]]（如生漆、黑漆、弁柄漆等），或將漆與金粉、銀粉或白金粉混合以修補破損陶器的日本技藝，是類似於「[[蒔繪|蒔繪]]」技藝的方法。<ref name="smashing">{{Citation|first=Blake|last=Gopnik|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2009/03/02/AR2009030202723.html|title=At Freer, Aesthetic Is Simply Smashing|journal=[[The_Washington_Post|The Washington Post]]|date=March 3, 2009}}.</ref><ref name="seams">{{Citation|publisher=Smithsonian|contribution-url=http://www.asia.si.edu/exhibitions/current/GoldenSeams.htm#|contribution=Golden Seams: The Japanese Art of Mending Ceramics|title=Freer Gallery of Art|access-date=3 March 2009|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090317021839/http://www.asia.si.edu/exhibitions/current/GoldenSeams.htm|archivedate=2009-03-17}}.</ref><ref name=":1">{{Cite web|title=Daijisen|url=http://kotobank.jp/word/%E9%87%91%E7%B6%99%E3%81%8E}}</ref>金繼作為一種哲學，是將破損和修補視為物件歷史的一部分，而非掩飾。<ref name=":2">{{Cite news|url=http://mymodernmet.com/kintsugi-kintsukuroi/|title=Kintsugi: The Centuries-Old Art of Repairing Broken Pottery with Gold|date=2017-04-25|work=My Modern Met|accessdate=2017-07-12|language=en-US}}</ref>

== 起源 ==
漆器在日本是悠久的傳統工藝。<ref>{{Cite web|title=Japan's Ancient Art of Lacquerware|url=https://www.nytimes.com/1985/09/22/travel/shopper-s-world-japan-s-ancient-art-of-lacquerware.html|author=Ota|date=September 22, 1985|first=Alan K.|work=[[New_York_Times|New York Times]]|publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=A Craft Polished to the Lofty Heights of Art|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2008/04/04/arts/design/04lacq.html|accessdate=April 5, 2014|author=Ken|date=April 4, 2008|first=Johnson|work=New York Times|publisher=}}</ref>在某些場合，金繼可能和「[[蒔繪|蒔繪]]」合併使用以替代其他陶瓷修補技術。儘管該工藝以日本工匠的手藝而知名，但該技術也用於其他國家，如中國、越南和韓國的陶瓷物件。<ref name=":12">{{Cite web|title=Golden Seams: The Japanese Art of Mending Ceramics|url=http://www.si.edu/Exhibitions/Details/Golden-Seams-The-Japanese-Art-of-Mending-Ceramics-4567|accessdate=2014-04-05|date=November 8, 2008|work=[[Smithsonian_(magazine)|Smithsonian]]}}</ref>
